10. Have, in accordance with the Health Insurance Portability
and Accountability Act (HIPAA), access to all data and systems
necessary to carry out the requirements of the consent decree in
Briggs et al v. Friesen et al, Case No. 23-CV-00081 (N.D. Okla. Mar.
10, 2025);
11. Have unrestricted access to the Data Support division and
information technology (IT) support in order to design and implement
dashboards necessary to design a competency continuum in Oklahoma;
12. Have control of all legislatively appropriated dollars
designated for the consent decree in Briggs et al v. Friesen et al,
Case No. 23-CV-00081 (N.D. Okla. Mar. 10, 2025); and
13. Prepare a detailed budget and regular reports or audits of
funds and deliver to the Oklahoma Legislature on a regular basis and
as requested.
SECTION 2. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
